text.section:
Means of mitigating loss include:
the installation of one or more of the following:
hurricane shutters;
secondary water barrier;
reinforced roof coverings;
braced gable ends;
reinforced roof to wall connections;
tie downs; and
reinforced opening protections;
repair or replacement of:
exterior doors, including garage doors;
hurricane resistant trusses, studs, and other structural components; and
repair or replacement of manufactured home piers, anchors, and tie down straps; and
any mitigation effort that materially mitigates loss from a hurricane or other storm otherwise covered under the policy.
